      <h3>Working Capital Reserve</h3>
      <p>Most operators underestimate how long it takes to reach break-even. Even a well-run dispensary typically needs 6-12 months of operating expenses in reserve. Budget $100,000-$250,000 in accessible working capital that isn't committed to build-out or inventory.</p>

      <Callout title="Total Startup Cost Range" type="warning">
        Fully loaded startup costs for a Maine dispensary range from approximately $360,000 on the conservative end (rural underserved market, owner-operator model, modest build-out) to $1,030,000 on the higher end (prime location, full build-out, significant initial inventory). Most operators fall in the $500,000-$700,000 range. Do not plan based on the low end — budget for contingencies and slower ramp-up.
      </Callout>

      <p>For a detailed breakdown of all cost categories, see our <a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-costs/">Maine Dispensary Costs guide</a>.</p>
